    "Deep TDA has demonstrated potential in a variety of challenging settings.",
    "The invariance of PH information to continuous deformation means TDA applies well to settings where objects should have consistent shapes but may be transformed in some way.",
    "TDA also performs well to bridge the gap between structural information and prior knowledge.",
    "If we have prior knowledge of the topology of a class of objects, then PDs are an effective tool for the classification and comparison of data against this class, even in the presence of noise or limited data.",
    "This robustness is well adapted to deep learning."
